/*
:name: nil_operand_nonarith
:type: error
:error: (nil|operand)
*/
// 2f-nil — nil is legal only as a direct-assignment RHS or in `==`/`!=`. A nil
// operand reaching ANY other operator (here a shift; same for < <= | & ~ >> etc.)
// is an illegal use of nil and must be reported, not silently folded. (The
// arithmetic `+` case is covered by adv_nil_operation.prp.)
const a = nil
const y = a << 2   // locate_error_here
cputs("y")
